The Netherlands sold 1 million
European Union spot carbon permits at 6.59 euros ($8.27) a
metric ton in an auction on the European Energy Exchange AG.  The country has sold 4 million tons of spot permits as part
of its allocation of carbon allowances in 2012. The EUâ€™s
emissions trading system is in its second phase, which runs from
2008 to the end of this year.  EEX has also auctioned Phase 2 permits on behalf of Germany
and  Lithuania , and is selling Phase 3 permits for delivery in
2013 for the  European Investment Bank .  To contact the reporter on this story:
